<DocsLayout title="Online Approval" section="Estimates">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Send estimates to customers for approval via email, text message, or PDF.
    The online approval process simplifies workflows and projects a professional image for your business.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Open the estimate you want to send</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Actions</strong> button to access sending options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Sending Options</h2>

  <h3>Option 1: Email Approval Link</h3>
  <img src="/images/estimates/onlineapproval_01.png" alt="Email Approval" />
  <ol>
    <li>From the Actions button, select <strong>Send for Approval</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Copy to Clipboard</strong> to copy the approval link</li>
    <li>Paste the link in your email to the customer</li>
    <li>Customer clicks the link to review and approve online</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    Customers can request changes or provide approval directly through the link.
    You'll receive an email notification when they respond.
  </p>

  <h3>Option 2: Text Message</h3>
  <img src="/images/estimates/onlineapproval_02.png" alt="Text Approval" />
  <ol>
    <li>From the Actions button, select <strong>Send via Text</strong></li>
    <li>The estimate link is sent directly to the customer's phone</li>
    <li>Customer can review and approve from their mobile device</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Option 3: PDF Download</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>From the Actions button, select <strong>PDF Estimate</strong></li>
    <li>Download the estimate as a PDF</li>
    <li>Attach to an email and send to the customer</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Customer Experience</h2>
  <p>When customers receive the approval link, they can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Review the estimate details and pricing</li>
    <li>Select optional products if offered</li>
    <li>Submit change requests</li>
    <li>Approve the estimate with an electronic signature</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You receive an <strong>email notification</strong> when a customer approves or requests changes</li>
    <li>Change requests include customer notes for review</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Double-check all details</strong> before sending â€” customers will see exactly what you've entered.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use text messages</strong> for faster responses, especially for mobile-savvy customers.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Follow up</strong> if you haven't received a response within a few days.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
